♪ I'LL BE READY

01:40.926 --> 01:43.886
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS

01:44.016 --> 01:47.019
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

02:00.729 --> 02:06.561
-[SOFT MUSIC]

02:27.799 --> 02:30.759
-GOOD JOB, APRIL.
THAT'S IT, KEEP GOING.

02:35.372 --> 02:36.721
PULL WITH YOUR BACK.

02:38.158 --> 02:40.464
GOOD, THAT WAS MUCH BETTER.

02:47.384 --> 02:49.908
-NEWMIE, WHY DON'T YOU
GUYS TRY ROWING TOGETHER?

02:50.039 --> 02:51.649
IT'S A TEAM SPORT!

02:51.780 --> 02:54.130
-YOU KNOW, YOU GUYS ARE
SHOOTING PEAS IN A BATTLESHIP.

02:54.261 --> 02:56.959
-SOMETIMES YOU JUST
HAVE TO ADMIT DEFEAT.

02:57.699 --> 03:01.224
EVEN BEFORE YOU
START. [LAUGHS]

03:07.970 --> 03:10.451
-WHY IS NEWMIE PRACTICING
WITH APRIL ANYWAY?

03:10.581 --> 03:11.495
-YOU DIDN'T HEAR?

03:12.235 --> 03:14.585
MITCH ISN'T GOING TO BE
IN THE RACE THIS YEAR.

03:15.717 --> 03:17.980
-I THOUGHT MITCH AND NEWMIE
WERE DEFENDING CHAMPIONS.

03:18.110 --> 03:20.722
-YEAH, THEY'VE WON THE
TAPLIN SOMETHING LIKE

03:20.852 --> 03:22.376
SEVEN YEARS IN A ROW.

03:22.898 --> 03:24.595
-SO WHY'D HE DROP OUT?

03:24.726 --> 03:26.641
-HE WANTS HOBIE TO
HAVE A SHOT OF HIS OWN

03:26.771 --> 03:28.164
AT WINNING THE TITLE.

03:28.730 --> 03:31.167
PLUS, I DON'T THINK
MITCH IS TOO THRILLED

03:31.298 --> 03:32.777
WITH BEING A CAPTAIN.

03:32.908 --> 03:34.605
-SO, HE CHOOSES APRIL
TO BE HIS NEW PARTNER?

03:34.736 --> 03:37.391
-YOU KNOW, NEWMIE,
THINKS HE CAN WIN THE RACE

03:37.521 --> 03:38.479
ALL BY HIMSELF.

03:39.306 --> 03:41.177
ONLY REASON SHE'S IN
THE BOAT IS BECAUSE

03:41.308 --> 03:43.092
THE RULES REQUIRE TWO
PEOPLE IN THE DORY.

03:43.223 --> 03:44.572
-NEWMIE.

03:50.621 --> 03:53.929
-[ENGINE ROARING]

03:56.453 --> 03:58.760
-HEY ARE THOSE ROW
BOATS OUT THERE?

03:58.890 --> 04:00.892
-THEY CAN'T EVEN SEE
WHERE THEY'RE GOING!

04:01.023 --> 04:02.981
-WELL, THEY'RE GONNA
KNOW WE'RE OUT HERE!

04:03.112 --> 04:04.592
-[LAUGHING]

04:04.722 --> 04:06.158
-GOOD OUT HERE.

04:11.468 --> 04:13.165
-OKAY, ALL TOGETHER.

04:14.297 --> 04:16.255
-APRIL: NEWMIE,
LOOK, HE'S NOT SLOWING.

04:20.172 --> 04:22.043
-CODY.
-CODY: WHAT'S UP?

04:24.176 --> 04:25.874
NEWMIE, APRIL!

04:27.179 --> 04:28.529
-NEWMIE: HE'S
HEADING RIGHT FOR US.

04:28.659 --> 04:34.361
-[SHOUTING]

04:35.666 --> 04:37.581
-MAN: WE'LL JUST
SCARE THEM A LITTLE.

04:37.712 --> 04:42.760
-[SHOUTING]

04:42.891 --> 04:45.241
-NEWMIE: CODY,
J.D. LOOK OUT!

04:48.897 --> 04:51.247
-[LAUGHING]

04:53.249 --> 04:54.598
APRIL, COME ON!

04:54.729 --> 04:56.078
-HEY!

04:56.208 --> 04:59.211
HEY, WATCH OUT!

04:59.342 --> 05:01.126
-OH, NO.

05:01.257 --> 05:02.780
-J.D.: HEY, MOVE IT!

05:04.347 --> 05:05.479
-[SHOUTING]

05:07.002 --> 05:07.959
-HEY!

05:17.621 --> 05:21.016
-[LAUGHING]

05:27.152 --> 05:28.240
-TURN THE WHEEL!

05:34.551 --> 05:37.424
-[SCREAMING]

05:47.390 --> 05:49.261
-OH, MY GOD. CODY!

05:49.392 --> 05:50.262
-LET'S GET 'EM!

05:50.393 --> 05:51.481
-J.D.: LET'S GO!

05:57.226 --> 05:58.183
I GOT YOU.

05:59.315 --> 06:00.185
-J.D. WHERE'S
THE OTHER GUY?

06:00.316 --> 06:01.186
-HE'S OVER THERE.

06:03.580 --> 06:05.060
I GOT YOU, I GOT YOU.

06:08.324 --> 06:10.195
-IT'S ALL RIGHT, MAN,
I GOT YOU. YOU OKAY?

06:10.326 --> 06:12.459
ALL RIGHT, HERE WE GO.

06:21.381 --> 06:23.121
-HOBIE: WHERE YOU GOING?

06:23.252 --> 06:24.732
-GOT A MEETING WITH THE COAST
GUARD ABOUT THOSE TWO GUYS

06:24.862 --> 06:27.691
WHO ALMOST KILLED CODY
AND J.D. YESTERDAY.

06:28.300 --> 06:30.433
DO ME A FAVOR WILL
YA? COOK DINNER?

06:30.564 --> 06:33.175
-WHY CAN'T YOU JUST PICK
SOMETHING ON THE WAY HOME?

06:33.305 --> 06:34.829
-'CAUSE WE HAVE
BEEN EATING JUNK FOOD

06:34.959 --> 06:36.483
FOR THE LAST TWO WEEKS.

06:36.613 --> 06:38.354
THE LEAST YOU COULD
DO IS COOK US DINNER.

06:38.485 --> 06:40.182
-COME ON, YOU KNOW
HOW LONG THAT TAKES.

06:40.312 --> 06:42.663
I JUST WORKED AN EIGHT
HOUR SHIFT, I'M EXHAUSTED.

06:42.793 --> 06:44.708
-OKAY, OKAY, YOU'RE
RIGHT. YOU NEED YOUR REST.

06:44.839 --> 06:45.622
I'LL COOK DINNER.

06:45.753 --> 06:46.928
-DAD.

06:47.058 --> 06:48.756
-NO, I'M SORRY,
IT WAS MY MISTAKE,

06:48.886 --> 06:50.018
I SHOULDN'T HAVE
EVEN ASKED.

06:50.148 --> 06:50.975
-HOBIE: DAD!

06:51.106 --> 06:52.020
-IT WON'T HAPPEN AGAIN.

06:52.150 --> 06:52.934
-DAD!

06:53.064 --> 06:54.457
-WHAT? WHAT?

06:54.588 --> 06:56.764
-WHAT DO YOU WANT?
MEXICAN OR CHINESE?

06:57.895 --> 06:58.896
-CHINESE.

07:01.638 --> 07:04.554
-EXCUSE ME, HAVE YOU
SEEN APRIL GIMINSKI?

07:04.685 --> 07:06.426
-YEAH, I JUST SAW
HER ON THE BEACH.

07:06.556 --> 07:08.689
-WELL, I'M HER BROTHER, CHARLIE,
AND THIS IS OUR MOM, PAIGE.

07:08.819 --> 07:09.733
-THANK YOU, CHARLIE.

07:09.864 --> 07:11.039
-HI, I'M MITCH BUCHANNON.

07:11.169 --> 07:12.997
-OH, YOU'RE
CAPTAIN BUCHANNON.

07:13.128 --> 07:14.825
APRIL'S TOLD
US ALL ABOUT YOU.

07:14.956 --> 07:16.566
-MY SON, HOBIE, HE'S A ROOKIE
LIFEGUARD AT ZUMA BEACH.

07:16.697 --> 07:18.394
-ZUMA? WHERE'S THAT?

07:18.525 --> 07:20.440
-IT'S JUST A LITTLE NORTH
OF HERE BEFORE COUNTY LINE.

07:20.570 --> 07:21.876
-WELL, WE'RE
FROM GREEN BAY.

07:22.006 --> 07:24.139
-OH, KILLER, I
LOVE THE PACKERS.

07:24.269 --> 07:27.359
-WHOA, LOOK AT THESE.
THEY'RE HUMONGOUS.

07:27.490 --> 07:29.492
-CHARLIE, THAT DOES
NOT BELONG TO YOU.

07:29.623 --> 07:31.059
-NO, NO, IT'S OKAY.

07:31.189 --> 07:32.800
THEY'RE BINOCULARS SO
WE CAN WATCH THE WATER.

07:32.930 --> 07:34.541
YOU CAN ACTUALLY SEE ALL
THE WAY OUT TO ZUMA BEACH.

07:34.671 --> 07:35.716
-CAN I LOOK THROUGH THEM?

07:35.846 --> 07:37.021
-MITCH: SURE, GO AHEAD.

07:37.152 --> 07:37.892
-HOBIE: I'LL GIVE
YOU A HAND.

07:38.501 --> 07:40.198
-CHARLIE'S BEEN
COOPED UP ALL WEEK.

07:40.329 --> 07:42.200
COULD HARDLY WAIT TO
COME TO THE BEACH.

07:42.984 --> 07:44.681
-FRESH AIR WILL BE
GOOD FOR HIM, HUH?

07:48.903 --> 07:51.427
APRIL SAYS HE'S UNDERGOING
SOME TESTS AT UCLA?

07:51.949 --> 07:55.083
-I GOT CANCER. THEY
CALL IT MEDULLARY THYROID

07:55.213 --> 07:56.606
OR SOMETHING LIKE THAT.

07:56.737 --> 07:58.478
-IT'S VERY RARE AND
STRIKES MOSTLY CHILDREN.

07:59.174 --> 08:00.262
-SUCKS, HUH?

08:00.392 --> 08:01.872
-YOU LOOK GOOD.

08:02.003 --> 08:03.439
-WELL, THEY STOPPED MY
CHEMO SIX MONTHS AGO,

08:03.570 --> 08:04.962
SO I GOT MY HAIR BACK.

08:05.572 --> 08:08.226
I'M THINKING ABOUT DYING IT
BLONDE AS LONG AS I'M IN LA.

08:08.357 --> 08:09.924
-WE'LL TALK ABOUT
THAT, CHARLIE.

08:10.054 --> 08:11.795
-ARE YOU STAYING
WITH APRIL?

08:11.926 --> 08:13.841
-UH-HUH, YEAH,
IT'S A BIT CRAMPED

08:13.971 --> 08:17.192
IN HER APARTMENT THOUGH AND
WE CAN'T AFFORD A HOTEL.

08:21.718 --> 08:23.764
APRIL! APRIL!

08:23.894 --> 08:25.722
I SEE APRIL! APRIL!

08:25.853 --> 08:28.290
APRIL! CAN WE GO DOWN
THERE, PLEASE, MOM?

08:28.420 --> 08:30.597
-YOU CAN HARDLY WAIT TO
GET YOUR TOES IN THE SAND.

08:31.423 --> 08:32.686
-I'LL TAKE HIM DOWN THERE.

08:37.821 --> 08:39.693
-HE'S QUITE A KID.
-PAIGE: YEAH.

08:43.653 --> 08:46.351
-AFTER YESTERDAY, I'M NOT
SURE I'M CUT OUT FOR THIS.

08:46.482 --> 08:47.875
-DON'T WORRY, ALL YOU
GOTTA DO IS LOOK GOOD.

08:48.005 --> 08:49.441
I'LL TAKE CARE
OF THE REST.

08:49.572 --> 08:50.704
HEY, GUYS, COULD YOU
BE CAREFUL WITH THAT?

08:50.834 --> 08:52.270
THAT'S OUR LAST DORY.

08:52.401 --> 08:54.534
-APRIL! APRIL!

08:55.404 --> 08:57.319
HEY, SIS!
-APRIL: HI!

08:58.842 --> 09:00.452
HEY, CHARLIE,
HOW YOU DOING?

09:00.583 --> 09:03.717
-WHAT A GREAT PLACE TO
WORK. YOU'RE SO LUCKY.

09:05.109 --> 09:07.024
-GUYS, I WANT YOU TO MEET
MY LITTLE BROTHER, CHARLIE.

09:07.155 --> 09:08.635
-HEY, CHARLIE.

09:08.765 --> 09:09.723
-WHAT'S UP, CHARLIE?

09:11.159 --> 09:12.247
-AND THIS MY MOTHER.

09:12.377 --> 09:13.640
-HOW DO YOU DO, PAIGE?

09:13.770 --> 09:15.337
-HI, PAIGE. J.D.

09:16.599 --> 09:18.340
-WHAT KIND OF
BOAT IS THAT?

09:20.124 --> 09:21.386
-THAT'S A DORY.

09:21.996 --> 09:23.998
-IN THE OLD DAYS,
LIFEGUARDS USED TO ROLL

09:24.128 --> 09:25.739
OUT TO THE SURF JUST TO
BE CLOSE TO THE SWIMMERS

09:25.869 --> 09:27.218
IN CASE THEY NEEDED HELP.

09:27.349 --> 09:29.046
-WELL, WHY DO YOU
STILL NEED THESE AROUND?

09:29.177 --> 09:31.832
-WE USE THEM TO RACE, WORK
OUT, ALL KINDS OF STUFF.

09:33.921 --> 09:35.575
-MOTHER, WHAT ARE
YOU DOING HERE?

09:35.705 --> 09:37.577
-THEY RELEASED
HIM EARLY TODAY.

09:37.707 --> 09:39.579
-I THOUGHT YOU SAID YOU
WEREN'T GOING TO BRING HIM HERE.

09:39.709 --> 09:41.537
-APRIL, HE'S
YOUR BROTHER.

09:44.409 --> 09:47.195
-WE GOT A BIG COMPETITION
COMING UP CALLED THE TAPLIN.

09:47.325 --> 09:48.370
WE'LL BE GOING
AGAINST LIFEGUARDS

09:48.500 --> 09:50.285
FROM ALL THE
OTHER BEACHES.

09:50.415 --> 09:51.634
-THAT'S COOL.

09:51.765 --> 09:53.201
-HEY, NEWMIE NEEDS
A NEW PARTNER.

09:53.331 --> 09:55.159
MAYBE YOU CAN TEACH
HIM THE ROPES.

09:55.290 --> 09:57.422
-WHAT DO YOU SAY, CHARLIE?
YOU WANNA GO FOR A ROW?

09:57.553 --> 09:59.642
-HE CAN'T GET WET.

09:59.773 --> 10:01.775
-I GOT A MORPHINE
DRIP IN MY STOMACH.

10:01.905 --> 10:03.690
IT USED TO BE IN
MY BACK UNTIL I GOT

10:03.820 --> 10:06.257
THIS REALLY
GROSS INFECTION.

10:06.388 --> 10:07.519
YOU GUYS WANNA SEE IT?

10:07.650 --> 10:08.608
-APRIL: THAT'S
OKAY, CHARLIE.

10:08.738 --> 10:10.174
-WELL, HOW ABOUT MY SCARS?

10:10.305 --> 10:12.437
THIS ONE WAS DONE BY
DR. RIKE AND THIS ONE

10:12.568 --> 10:15.179
WAS DONE BY
DR. BLOOMINGTHAL.

10:15.310 --> 10:18.008
I WAS IN SURGERY FOR
SIX HOURS WITH THIS ONE.

10:19.749 --> 10:21.882
-HI, GUYS. YOU
MUST BE CHARLIE.

10:22.012 --> 10:22.796
-CHARLIE: YEAH.

10:22.926 --> 10:23.710
-LIEUTENANT WALSH.

10:23.840 --> 10:25.189
-NICE TO MEET YOU.

10:25.320 --> 10:26.147
-SO, MITCH TOLD ME
THAT YOU GUYS MIGHT

10:26.277 --> 10:27.104
NEED A PLACE TO STAY?

10:28.062 --> 10:29.977
-OH, WE'RE FINE, REALLY.

10:30.107 --> 10:31.805
-YOU CAN STAY
AT MY PLACE.

10:31.935 --> 10:33.633
I'M GOING TO BE IN SAN DIEGO
ALL WEEK FOR A CONFERENCE.

10:33.763 --> 10:35.417
I JUST GAVE
MITCH THE KEYS.

10:36.244 --> 10:38.942
I THINK YOU'LL LIKE
IT, IT'S BY THE WATER.

10:43.120 --> 10:45.732
-OKAY, DON'T LOOK,
DON'T LOOK, DON'T LOOK.

10:45.862 --> 10:48.822
OKAY? LOOK.

10:50.214 --> 10:53.565
-AWESOME, WE GET TO
STAY HERE ON THIS BOAT?

10:53.696 --> 10:56.133
-MITCH: IN A WORD? YES.

10:56.264 --> 10:57.569
[LAUGHING]

10:57.700 --> 10:58.962
-I'LL SHOW HIM AROUND.
-MITCH: THANKS.

11:02.574 --> 11:03.880
-I DON'T KNOW
WHAT TO SAY.

11:04.402 --> 11:06.100
-I DON'T EITHER.

11:06.230 --> 11:07.492
MOM, I CAN'T BELIEVE YOU'RE
DOING THIS TO MY FRIENDS.

11:07.623 --> 11:08.755
-WHAT?

11:08.885 --> 11:10.452
-LAYING THIS
GUILT TRIP,

11:10.582 --> 11:12.280
DUMPING OUR
PROBLEMS OUT ON THEM!

11:12.410 --> 11:14.586
-WAIT A MINUTE, APRIL, THAT'S
NOT WHAT'S HAPPENING HERE.

11:14.717 --> 11:16.806
-MY FAMILY IS NOT
A CHARITY CASE.

11:16.937 --> 11:18.416
-THE BOAT ISN'T
BEING USED.

11:18.547 --> 11:19.896
TAYLOR WAS GLAD
TO GIVE IT TO US.

11:20.027 --> 11:21.463
-APRIL.

11:22.072 --> 11:24.422
-WE CANNOT STAY HERE.
-MITCH: WHY NOT?

11:25.423 --> 11:26.511
-TELL HIM, MOM.

11:28.513 --> 11:30.690
MY MOTHER HASN'T BEEN
COMPLETELY HONEST WITH YOU.

11:30.820 --> 11:32.039
-PLEASE DON'T.

11:32.169 --> 11:33.736
-TELL HIM, MOM,
TELL HIM THE TRUTH.

11:33.867 --> 11:35.869
TELL HIM ABOUT CHARLIE
AND WHY YOU'RE HERE.

11:36.696 --> 11:40.090
THERE'S NO TREATMENT FOR
CHARLIE. THERE'S NO HELP.

11:40.221 --> 11:43.746
HE'S ONLY GOING TO UCLA
TO BE A GUINEA PIG.

11:43.877 --> 11:45.661
THEY'RE ONLY GOING TO
STUDY HIM WHILE...

11:45.792 --> 11:47.402
WHILE HE DIES!

11:54.409 --> 11:58.239
-[SOFT MUSIC]

11:58.369 --> 12:00.067
-MITCH: HEY, HOBSTER!

12:00.197 --> 12:02.983
CODY SAID YOU WANTED
TO SEE ME, WHAT'S UP?

12:03.113 --> 12:05.246
-YEAH, ACTUALLY, I
CAME BY TO SEE APRIL.

12:05.376 --> 12:07.204
SHE SEEMED
PRETTY SKETCHED OUT.

12:07.335 --> 12:09.511
-YEAH, SHE'S NOT
DOING TOO GOOD, PAL.

12:09.641 --> 12:11.818
LET ME TELL YOU, WENT
THROUGH A LOT OF PAIN

12:11.948 --> 12:13.776
WATCHING HER BROTHER
DIE, CAN'T BE EASY.

12:13.907 --> 12:14.995
-YEAH.

12:15.125 --> 12:16.910
-SO, WHAT'S ON YOUR MIND?

12:17.040 --> 12:17.998
-I GOTTA QUESTION.

12:18.128 --> 12:20.174
-WELL, I GOT AN ANSWER.

12:20.304 --> 12:22.916
-THEY SAY YOU'RE NOT
GONNA RACE IN THE TAPLIN.

12:23.046 --> 12:24.265
-THEY ARE RIGHT.

12:24.395 --> 12:25.832
-HOBIE: YOU GOT A REASON?

12:25.962 --> 12:26.528
-MITCH: NOPE, YOU GOT
A PROBLEM WITH THAT?

12:26.658 --> 12:28.051
-YEAH, I DO!

12:28.182 --> 12:29.879
-ALL RIGHT, HOBSTER,
I'LL TELL YOU THE TRUTH.

12:30.010 --> 12:33.143
I WANNA WATCH MY SON'S FIRST
TAPLIN NOT BEAT HIM IN IT.

12:33.274 --> 12:34.928
-BUT I WANNA RACE YOU.

12:35.058 --> 12:39.454
-YOU DO? OH, WHAT, YOU PLAN
ON WINNING IT I TAKE IT?

12:39.584 --> 12:40.368
-HOBIE: YOU GOT IT.

12:40.498 --> 12:41.369
-[LAUGHING]

12:41.499 --> 12:42.849
COME ON, DAD, RACE ME.

12:42.979 --> 12:44.328
-NO, HOBSTER, IT'S
TIME TO PASS THE TORCH

12:44.459 --> 12:46.940
FROM ONE GENERATION OF
BUCHANNONS TO THE NEXT.

12:47.070 --> 12:48.855
-THEY WERE RIGHT,
YOU ARE CHICKEN.

12:48.985 --> 12:50.117
-OH, RIGHT, YOU'RE
GONNA TRY AND BAIT ME

12:50.247 --> 12:51.422
WITH THE OLD
CHICKEN LINE.

12:51.553 --> 12:52.859
WELL, I'M MUCH TOO
MATURE FOR THAT.

12:52.989 --> 12:54.121
-HEY, IF YOU DON'T
WANT TO RACE BECAUSE

12:54.251 --> 12:55.078
YOU'RE AFRAID
YOU'LL LOSE--

12:55.209 --> 12:56.036
-I'M SEVEN TIME CHAMP.

12:56.863 --> 12:58.429
YOU DON'T WANT A PIECE
OF ME, GRASSHOPPER.

12:58.560 --> 13:00.823
-IF I WANT TO BE THE BEST,
I GOTTA BEAT THE BEST.

13:00.954 --> 13:02.869
-IS THAT WHAT THEY SAY?

13:02.999 --> 13:04.479
-YUP AND I AGREE.

13:04.609 --> 13:10.224
-WELL, FOR ONCE, THEY
ARE RIGHT. YOU'RE ON.

13:10.354 --> 13:11.791
-ALL RIGHT!

13:11.921 --> 13:13.096
HEY, I SEE CHARLIE,
I'M GONNA GO SAY HI.

13:13.227 --> 13:14.010
GOOD LUCK.

13:14.141 --> 13:15.403
-[MITCH LAUGHING]

13:18.798 --> 13:20.712
-IT'S PRETTY NICE
OUT HERE, HUH?

13:22.279 --> 13:23.585
HAVE YOU EVER BEEN
ON A GRUNION RUN?

13:23.715 --> 13:25.239
-NO, BUT I'VE
HEARD OF THEM.

13:25.369 --> 13:26.893
I THOUGHT THEY
ONLY RUN AT NIGHT.

13:27.023 --> 13:28.633
-WELL, THEY DO, BUT
SOMETIMES THEY GET CAUGHT

13:28.764 --> 13:30.157
IN THESE LITTLE
TIDE POOLS.

13:30.287 --> 13:31.636
I'LL SHOW YOU.

13:38.165 --> 13:41.168
SEE? DURING THE
SPRING AND SUMMER

13:41.298 --> 13:43.823
WHEN THE TIDE COMES UP
HIGH, THE GRUNIONS THEY COME

13:43.953 --> 13:44.954
UP AND THEY
MATE IN THE SAND.

13:45.694 --> 13:47.000
IT'S FUN TO TRY TO CATCH
THEM WITH YOUR HANDS.

13:47.130 --> 13:48.523
-CAN I HOLD IT?

13:48.653 --> 13:50.873
-YEAH, BE CAREFUL DON'T
SQUEEZE IT TOO HARD,

13:51.004 --> 13:52.092
IT'LL SLIP THROUGH
YOUR FINGERS.

13:53.528 --> 13:55.573
-[CHARLIE LAUGHING]

13:56.792 --> 13:57.837
-COOL.

13:57.967 --> 13:59.229
-YOU WANNA
KNOW WHAT THE

13:59.360 --> 14:00.796
COOLEST THING ABOUT
GRUNIONS ARE?

14:00.927 --> 14:02.102
THEY MATE WITHOUT EVEN
TOUCHING EACH OTHER.

14:02.232 --> 14:03.625
-HOW DO THEY DO THAT?

14:03.755 --> 14:06.933
-WELL, THE FEMALE,
SHE WASHES UP ON SHORE

14:07.063 --> 14:08.804
AND SHE LAYS HER EGGS.

14:08.935 --> 14:11.198
THEN, THE MALE, HE COMES UP
AND HE FERTILIZES THE EGGS.

14:11.328 --> 14:14.375
ON THE NEXT WAVE, THEY
BOTH WASH BACK OUT TO SEA

14:14.505 --> 14:16.551
AND THEY LEAVE
THEIR EGGS BEHIND

14:16.681 --> 14:18.074
TO BE LITTLE
GRUNION BABIES.

14:18.205 --> 14:20.598
-I CAN'T BELIEVE THEY
NEVER TOUCH EACH OTHER.

14:20.729 --> 14:22.165
-IT'S PRETTY WEIRD, HUH?

14:22.296 --> 14:25.212
-[GIRLS LAUGHING]

14:28.389 --> 14:30.130
-I'M SURE GLAD
I'M NOT A GRUNION.

14:30.260 --> 14:31.914
-[HOBIE CHUCKLING]

14:32.045 --> 14:34.656
SO, WHO DO YOU THINK THE
PRETTIEST GIRL OUT HERE IS?

14:35.918 --> 14:36.788
-MY MOM.

14:38.181 --> 14:39.356
IT'S TIME FOR
YOU TO GO HOME.

14:46.407 --> 14:51.716
-[SIRENS SCREECHING]

14:55.024 --> 14:56.678
-GO AHEAD, HIT
THE SIREN AGAIN.

14:56.808 --> 14:57.984
DIDN'T HEAR IT
IN GREEN BAY.

14:58.114 --> 15:00.247
-[SIRENS SCREECHING]

15:00.377 --> 15:02.727
HEY, CHECK THIS OUT.

15:02.858 --> 15:04.033
COME ON, COME ON.

15:09.517 --> 15:10.822
CHECK IT OUT.

15:10.953 --> 15:12.302
-CAN I GO IN?
-MITCH: SURE.

15:17.786 --> 15:19.222
-MOM, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

15:19.353 --> 15:20.571
-PAIGE: CHARLIE WANTED
TO SEE THE EQUIPMENT

15:20.702 --> 15:22.138
ON THE CALL CAR--

15:22.269 --> 15:23.618
-THIS ISN'T A MOVIE
STUDIO OR DISNEYLAND,

15:23.748 --> 15:25.054
THIS IS WHERE I WORK.

15:25.185 --> 15:26.447
I MEAN, YOU CAN'T
JUST BARGE IN HERE

15:26.577 --> 15:28.231
AND EXPECT A GUIDED TOUR.

15:28.362 --> 15:30.842
-I'M SORRY, APRIL.
IT WAS MY IDEA.

15:33.149 --> 15:35.369
-HEY, WHY DON'T YOU AND YOUR
MOM HEAD DOWN TO THE BEACH

15:35.499 --> 15:37.545
AND CHECK OUT THE SURF SKI,
I'LL BE RIGHT THERE, HUH?

15:37.675 --> 15:39.155
-SURE.
-MITCH: COOL.

15:40.809 --> 15:41.941
-CHARLIE: LET'S GO, MOM.

15:43.203 --> 15:44.595
-MITCH, I'M SORRY.

15:44.726 --> 15:46.336
YOU SHOULDN'T HAVE
TO WASTE YOUR TIME

15:46.467 --> 15:48.686
WITH MY FAMILY JUST BECAUSE
YOU FEEL SORRY FOR THEM.

15:48.817 --> 15:51.602
-COME HERE. SIT DOWN.

15:53.213 --> 15:55.345
ALL RIGHT, LOOK, LET'S
GET SOMETHING STRAIGHT.

15:55.476 --> 15:59.871
CHARLIE IS NOT AT BAYWATCH
BECAUSE I FEEL SORRY FOR HIM.

16:00.002 --> 16:01.656
HE'S HERE BECAUSE
WE LIKE HIM.

16:01.786 --> 16:06.269
-WELL, IT'S JUST THAT HE
CAN KIND OF BRING YOU DOWN.

16:06.400 --> 16:09.794
-NOT ME, YOUR
BROTHER INSPIRES ME.

16:09.925 --> 16:12.493
HE REMINDS ME WHAT
COURAGE IS ALL ABOUT.

16:12.623 --> 16:15.452
YOUR MOM TOLD ME HE
CAME DOWN TO UCLA

16:15.583 --> 16:18.238
TO UNDERGO TESTS
BECAUSE MAYBE JUST MAYBE

16:18.368 --> 16:20.457
HE COULD SAVE
ANOTHER CHILD'S LIFE.

16:21.154 --> 16:25.027
TO ME, THAT QUALIFIES
HIM AS A HERO.

16:25.158 --> 16:30.206
NOW, IF HE WANTS TO HANG
OUT IN A CALL CAR OR A TOWER

16:30.337 --> 16:34.254
OR CHECK OUT A SURF
SKI, THAT'S FINE BY ME.

16:35.690 --> 16:38.258
-[SOMBER MUSIC]

16:42.262 --> 16:47.006
-♪ DID YOU KNOW YOU INSPIRE ME?

16:47.136 --> 16:52.489
♪ TO FIND MY COURAGE WHEN I AM WEAK

16:52.620 --> 16:57.581
♪ TO FIND ELUSIVE SERENITY

16:57.712 --> 16:59.975
♪ STILL I SEARCH

17:00.106 --> 17:03.109
♪ STILL I SEEK

17:04.109 --> 17:08.417
♪ YOU CALL US SAVIORS FOR WHAT WE DO

17:08.549 --> 17:14.337
♪ ALL THE WHILE YOU KNEW
♪ THAT WE COULDN'T SAVE YOU

17:15.077 --> 17:19.646
♪ WITH STRENGTH AND GRACE
♪ HOW YOU MAKE US PROUD

17:19.777 --> 17:24.086
♪ FOR YOU WE'RE LIVING RIGHT NOW

17:25.869 --> 17:30.484
♪ SINCE I MET YOU YOU'VE HELPED ME SEE

17:31.093 --> 17:36.185
♪ THE BEAUTY RIGHT HERE IN FRONT OF ME ♪

17:36.838 --> 17:41.495
♪ AFRAID TO FEEL, EMOTIONS KEPT AT BAY ♪

17:42.322 --> 17:46.195
♪ NOW I LIVE FOR TODAY

17:47.718 --> 17:52.027
♪ YOU CALL US SAVIORS FOR WHAT WE DO

17:52.158 --> 17:57.902
♪ ALL THE WHILE YOU KNEW
♪ THAT WE COULDN'T SAVE YOU

17:58.033 --> 18:03.256
♪ WITH STRENGTH AND GRACE
♪ HOW YOU MAKE US PROUD

18:03.821 --> 18:07.564
♪ FOR YOU WE'RE LIVING RIGHT NOW ♪

18:08.435 --> 18:10.524
♪ YOU ARE YOUNG

18:12.134 --> 18:16.138
♪ BUT YOU'RE NOT A CHILD HOLD YOUR CARE

18:17.052 --> 18:21.578
♪ WITH AN EASY SMILE YOU INSPIRE

18:22.753 --> 18:25.147
♪ WITH SELFLESS LOVE

18:25.974 --> 18:30.196
♪ YOU ARE THE HERO YOU'VE ♪
♪ BEEN DREAMING OF

18:30.326 --> 18:32.198
♪ BODY'S WEAK

18:33.677 --> 18:37.942
♪ BUT YOUR SPIRIT'S STRONG
♪ SHARE YOUR LIGHT

18:39.118 --> 18:43.339
♪ WITH A HOPEFUL SONG SPENT YOUR LIFE

18:44.558 --> 18:46.864
♪ WITHOUT A CURE

18:47.691 --> 18:52.957
♪ BECOMING THE RESCUE ♪
♪ YOU WERE WAITING FOR

18:53.088 --> 18:57.223
♪ THROUGH ALL THESE THINGS YOU'VE SHOWN

18:58.702 --> 19:02.141
♪ THE BRAVEST HEART I'VE KNOWN

19:04.926 --> 19:06.057
-[CODY GRUNTING]

19:07.798 --> 19:10.279
-HEARD THAT HOBIE'S GOT A
NEW PARTNER FOR THE TAPLIN.

19:10.410 --> 19:13.108
-SO WHAT? NO ROOKIE'S
GONNA BEAT US, KID.

19:13.891 --> 19:15.066
-IT'S INGO.

19:15.197 --> 19:18.505
-THE AUSSIE? SNAILS, MAN.

19:18.635 --> 19:20.333
I SHOULD'VE
THOUGHT OF HIM.

19:21.029 --> 19:23.118
-THANKS A LOT, PARTNER.

19:23.249 --> 19:24.293
-[LAUGHING]

19:24.424 --> 19:25.512
-HEY, GUYS.
-CODY: HEY.

19:25.642 --> 19:26.730
-HAVE YOU SEEN, CHARLIE?

19:26.861 --> 19:29.994
-YEAH, THERE HE IS.

19:32.867 --> 19:34.608
-OH, MY GOSH,
WHAT IS HE DOING?

19:34.738 --> 19:36.392
HOW COULD HE TAKE
HIM OUT ON THE WATER?

19:36.523 --> 19:37.698
-YOUR MOM SAID
IT WAS OKAY.

19:37.828 --> 19:39.308
-BUT HE CAN'T GET WET.

19:39.439 --> 19:41.615
-DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT,
WE GOT HIM A DRY SUIT.

19:42.746 --> 19:44.444
-WHAT DO YOU
MEAN A DRY SUIT?

19:44.574 --> 19:46.620
-WELL, IT'S SOMETHING THE
COAST GUARD USES SOMETIMES.

19:47.186 --> 19:49.188
YOU CAN GO INTO THE WATER
BUT YOU WON'T GET WET.

19:49.927 --> 19:50.754
IT'S FINE.

19:52.539 --> 19:53.366
-OKAY.

20:02.853 --> 20:05.334
-HEY, APRIL! LOOK AT ME!

20:05.987 --> 20:08.598
-I SEE YOU, CHARLIE!
ARE YOU OKAY?

20:08.729 --> 20:10.687
-YEAH, COME ON
OUT WITH US!

20:26.616 --> 20:28.052
SO, HOW DO I LOOK?

20:28.183 --> 20:29.184
-LIKE A LIFEGUARD.

20:29.315 --> 20:30.881
-YOU READY TO GO?

20:31.795 --> 20:33.014
HANG ON!

20:38.324 --> 20:40.804
-[SOFT MUSIC]

20:40.935 --> 20:43.851
-THANKS, SIS, FOR ALL THE
COOL STUFF YOU'VE DONE FOR ME.

20:43.981 --> 20:47.376
BEING HERE AT BAYWATCH,
IT'S THE MOST FUN I'VE HAD

20:47.507 --> 20:48.725
IN MY WHOLE LIFE.

20:48.856 --> 20:50.684
-WELL, I'M GLAD
YOU CAME.

20:50.814 --> 20:52.990
-I'M JUST GLAD THAT
I COULD BE HERE.

20:53.687 --> 20:56.167
-HEY, CHARLIE!
YOU READY TO DRIVE?

20:56.298 --> 20:57.473
-DRIVE?

20:57.604 --> 20:59.040
-COME ON! IT'S ALL YOURS!

21:09.006 --> 21:11.226
-WOO! [CHUCKLES]

21:12.488 --> 21:16.536
CHARLIE, HEAD TOWARDS THE
JETTY RIGHT THERE. WOO!

21:16.666 --> 21:19.756
THOUGHT YOU SAID YOU COULDN'T
DRIVE, YOU'RE A NATURAL.

21:25.762 --> 21:27.416
WHERE'S THE MUSIC?

21:27.547 --> 21:29.984
-DISPATCH: CODE THREE,
POSSIBLE HEART ATTACK. 1,200.

21:30.114 --> 21:31.464
-WAIT A SECOND.

21:31.594 --> 21:33.901
-DISPATCH: I REPEAT
1,200 MARINA WAY.

21:34.031 --> 21:35.511
WHAT'S YOUR ETA PLEASE?

21:35.642 --> 21:37.426
-LIFEGUARD: ROGER,
DISPATCH ETA SEVEN MINUTES.

21:37.557 --> 21:39.254
-NO WAY THE MTS WILL
BE THERE IN TIME.

21:39.385 --> 21:40.821
CALL IT IN,
WE'RE RESPONDING.

21:40.951 --> 21:42.301
COME ON, CHARLIE,
WE'RE GOING TO WORK!

21:43.693 --> 21:45.782
-BAYWATCH, THIS IS
GIMINSKI IN WINDJET THREE.

21:45.913 --> 21:47.828
WE'RE RESPONDING TO CODE THREE
FROM THE POLICE DEPARTMENT.

21:47.958 --> 21:53.181
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

22:09.197 --> 22:10.546
-APRIL, STAY WITH CHARLIE.

22:10.677 --> 22:11.678
-OKAY.

22:15.638 --> 22:18.162
-L.A. COUNTY LIFEGUARD.
WHERE'S THE VICTIM?

22:18.293 --> 22:20.295
-GOD, YOU GUYS ARE
FAST. HE'S RIGHT HERE.

22:23.994 --> 22:25.518
-EXCUSE ME,
COMING THROUGH.

22:26.519 --> 22:28.825
-NO PULSE, NO BREATHING.

22:28.956 --> 22:30.000
WE GIVE HIM ONE MAN CPR.

22:30.827 --> 22:32.263
-[MUMBLING ON MACHINE]

22:32.394 --> 22:36.180
WE GOT A WHITE MALE, 50
YEARS OLD, CAUCASIAN,

22:37.399 --> 22:39.488
CARDIAC ARREST.
-APRIL: ONE, TWO...

22:39.619 --> 22:40.968
-CONTINUING CPR.

22:41.098 --> 22:45.451
-FOUR, FIVE, SIX,
SEVEN, EIGHT, NINE,

22:45.581 --> 22:49.368
10, 11, 12, 13, 14.

22:49.498 --> 22:51.631
-DEFIBRILLATOR: CANNOT CATCH
PATIENT. ANALYZING RHYTHM.

22:51.761 --> 22:54.808
CHARGING. PUSH FLASHING
BUTTON TO RESCUE.

22:56.723 --> 22:57.767
ANALYZING RHYTHM.

23:00.553 --> 23:01.728
-[BEEPING]

23:01.858 --> 23:04.687
CHECK PULSE. IF NO
PULSE, GIVE CPR.

23:06.907 --> 23:10.301
-HE HAS A PULSE.
HE'S BREATHING.

23:12.869 --> 23:14.175
-MAN: EXCUSE ME, SIR?

23:14.305 --> 23:16.786
-HE'S GOT A PULSE,
HE'S BREATHING.

23:21.530 --> 23:27.493
-♪ I WANNA MAKE A
DIFFERENCE IN THIS WORLD ♪

23:29.190 --> 23:32.759
♪ I WANT TO STAY STRONG

23:32.889 --> 23:36.415
♪ AND SEE THINGS
COME ALONG ♪

23:37.111 --> 23:38.112
♪ TO MAKE

23:38.939 --> 23:40.549
-IT'S FUNNY.

23:40.680 --> 23:41.724
WHEN HE WAS A KID WE USED
TO HAVE TO BRIBE CHARLIE

23:41.855 --> 23:43.552
TO GO TO MUSIC LESSONS.

23:43.683 --> 23:46.686
HE DIDN'T START WRITING SONGS
UNTIL AFTER HE GOT SICK.

23:48.252 --> 23:50.254
GUESS HE HAD SOMETHING
HE NEEDED TO SAY.

23:52.648 --> 23:54.345
-GREAT SONG, CHARLIE.

23:54.476 --> 23:56.391
-IT WAS REALLY GOOD, MAN.
YOU WANNA HEAR THE PLAYBACK?

23:56.522 --> 23:58.175
-NO, I THINK I'M
GONNA GET SOME REST,

23:58.306 --> 23:59.612
SO I CAN COME WATCH
YOU WIN TOMORROW.

23:59.742 --> 24:01.483
-ALL RIGHT, YOU PROMISE?
-CHARLIE: PROMISE.

24:01.614 --> 24:03.442
-[LAUGHS] GOOD LUCK.

24:04.443 --> 24:05.835
HOW LONG HAVE YOU
BEEN WORKING ON THAT?

24:05.966 --> 24:09.056
-I STARTED THE LAST TIME
I WAS IN THE HOSPITAL.

24:09.186 --> 24:11.145
I JUST WANT THE OTHER
SICK KIDS TO KNOW THAT

24:12.320 --> 24:14.365
EVEN IF YOU DON'T
HAVE A LOT OF TIME,

24:14.496 --> 24:15.802
YOU COULD STILL
MAKE A DIFFERENCE.

24:17.281 --> 24:18.457
-IT'S A GOOD
MESSAGE, MAN.

24:18.587 --> 24:20.067
EVERYBODY CAN
MAKE A DIFFERENCE.

24:20.197 --> 24:23.505
-I MEAN A REAL DIFFERENCE.
LIKE YOU GUYS DO.

24:23.636 --> 24:27.553
I MEAN, HOW DID IT FEEL SAVING
THAT GUY IN THE RESTAURANT?

24:27.683 --> 24:28.989
-YOU TELL US.

24:29.119 --> 24:30.294
-CHARLIE: WHAT ARE
YOU TALKING ABOUT?

24:30.425 --> 24:32.558
-I MEAN HE'S ALIVE
BECAUSE OF YOU.

24:32.688 --> 24:34.473
IF WE HADN'T BEEN
OUT THERE WITH YOU,

24:34.603 --> 24:36.997
WE WOULDN'T HAVE RESPONDED TO
THAT EMERGENCY CALL IN TIME.

24:37.127 --> 24:38.781
-GET OUT OF HERE.

24:38.912 --> 24:40.783
-MY DAD'S RIGHT, LUCKY FOR
THAT GUY YOU WERE PLAYING

24:40.914 --> 24:42.263
WITH THE RADIO.

24:42.393 --> 24:44.439
-THAT'S REALLY REACHING,
BUT I'LL TAKE IT.

24:44.570 --> 24:46.572
-[HOBIE LAUGHING]

24:47.529 --> 24:52.708
-[CHATTERING]

25:15.209 --> 25:16.558
-ARE YOU KIDDING ME?

25:16.689 --> 25:18.038
MITCH AND NEWMIE?

25:19.518 --> 25:20.954
YOU GUYS ARE
BACK IN THE RACE?

25:21.084 --> 25:24.610
-THAT'S RIGHT, GET
READY TO EAT OUR WAKE.

25:24.740 --> 25:28.091
-CODY, CHECK THIS BABY
OUT. STATE OF THE ART.

25:28.875 --> 25:29.702
WHERE'D THIS COME FROM?

25:30.485 --> 25:31.834
-FRIENDS IN HIGH PLACES.

25:32.705 --> 25:34.924
-DAD, I THOUGHT YOU WANTED
TO BEAT ME FAIR AND SQUARE.

25:35.055 --> 25:36.622
WHAT'S WITH THE NEW
FANCY EQUIPMENT?

25:36.752 --> 25:38.754
-BAD LUCK, HOBSTER.

25:38.885 --> 25:41.061
WHEN J.D. AND CODY
WRECKED ONE OF THE DORIES,

25:41.191 --> 25:43.977
I REPLACED IT
WITH THIS ONE.

25:44.107 --> 25:45.544
-LISTEN, WHY DON'T YOU
GUYS GO BACK AND POLISH

25:45.674 --> 25:47.241
THAT WRECK OF YOURS?

25:47.371 --> 25:48.721
-HEY, ISN'T THE ANCIENT
MARINERS RACE NEXT WEEKEND?

25:48.851 --> 25:50.026
-[LAUGHING]

25:50.157 --> 25:51.245
-GO ON.

25:51.811 --> 25:57.556
-[SOFT MUSIC]

26:27.498 --> 26:29.849
-CHARLIE'S STILL ASLEEP, HE
HAD KIND OF A ROUGH NIGHT.

26:29.979 --> 26:32.547
I DON'T THINK HE'S
GONNA BE ABLE TO COME.

26:32.678 --> 26:35.071
-HE WAS REALLY LOOKING
FORWARD TO THIS RACE.

26:35.594 --> 26:37.596
-HE'S NOT THAT STRONG.

26:37.726 --> 26:38.945
I DON'T THINK
HE'S UP TO IT.

26:39.075 --> 26:42.426
-I'M READY, APRIL.
I'VE GOT IT ON.

26:44.428 --> 26:47.388
-CHARLIE, MAYBE YOU
SHOULD STAY IN BED.

26:48.519 --> 26:50.347
-I'VE GOT TO GO
TO THE RACE.

26:50.478 --> 26:52.219
I'VE GOT MY DRY SUIT
ON AND EVERYTHING.

26:52.828 --> 26:54.221
I'M ALL READY TO GO.

26:54.787 --> 26:56.397
-CHARLIE, WHEN
YOU'RE FEELING BETTER,

26:56.527 --> 26:57.833
THERE WILL BE
OTHER RACES.

26:57.964 --> 26:59.835
-WHAT IF THERE AREN'T
ANY OTHER RACES?

26:59.966 --> 27:02.621
WHAT IF THIS IS
MY LAST CHANCE?

27:02.751 --> 27:05.667
I PROMISED. I
PROMISED HOBIE.

27:07.103 --> 27:09.758
-[MELANCHOLY MUSIC]

27:12.239 --> 27:13.109
-OKAY, CHAMP.

27:14.981 --> 27:17.940
LET ME ZIP YOU UP. WE'RE
GOING TO THE RACES.

27:24.381 --> 27:26.035
-CAN I DRIVE?

27:26.166 --> 27:27.646
-SURE.

27:32.433 --> 27:36.045
MOM, I'M SORRY I'VE MADE
THIS EVEN HARDER ON YOU.

27:36.176 --> 27:38.874
-IT'S OKAY. I LOVE YOU.

27:49.493 --> 27:50.364
-LET'S GO.

27:52.627 --> 27:55.151
-ANNOUNCER: GOOD MORNING
AND WELCOME TO THE 32ND

27:55.282 --> 27:57.066
ANNUAL TAPLIN RACE.

27:57.197 --> 28:02.202
THIS IS A 16 TWO LAP DORY RACE
AROUND HISTORIC MALIBU PIER.

28:02.332 --> 28:05.031
OUR BEACHES REPRESENTED
TODAY ARE BAYWATCH

28:05.161 --> 28:09.122
WITH TWO TEAMS, ZUMA,
LEGS, CATALINA AND MALIBU.

28:10.950 --> 28:13.517
COME ON, READY
IN YOUR BOATS.

28:14.823 --> 28:16.303
-MAN: CODY!

28:16.433 --> 28:17.957
-ANNOUNCER: STERN MEN
TO THE STARTING LINE.

28:18.871 --> 28:20.046
TAKE YOUR MARKS,

28:20.916 --> 28:23.310
GET SET, GO!

28:23.440 --> 28:24.833
-[THRILLING MUSIC]

28:24.964 --> 28:26.748
A GOOD, CLEAN START!

28:32.406 --> 28:33.973
-COME ON, GO, GO, GO!

28:37.019 --> 28:38.891
-ANNOUNCER: FIRST TO BREAK
THE SURF LINE ARE SEVEN TIME

28:39.021 --> 28:42.024
CHAMPIONS, MITCH BUCHANNON
AND MICHAEL NEWMAN

28:42.155 --> 28:43.765
IN BAYWATCH ONE.

28:43.896 --> 28:45.941
THEY ARE HEAVILY FAVORED
TODAY TO BRING HOME THE TROPHY

28:46.072 --> 28:48.770
FOR THE EIGHTH
CONSECUTIVE YEAR.

28:48.901 --> 28:50.554
THEY HAVE THEIR WORK
CUT OUT FOR THEM.

28:50.685 --> 28:54.167
CLOSING IN IS BAYWATCH
TWO MANNED BY CODY MADISON

28:54.297 --> 28:56.125
AND J.D. DARIUS.

29:12.838 --> 29:15.275
INCHING INTO CONTENTION
ARE ZUMA'S ROOKIES

29:15.405 --> 29:17.843
HOBIE BUCHANNON
AND INGO DAWINGS.

29:17.973 --> 29:22.238
GIVING THE TWO LEAD TEAMS
SOME GOOD SOLID COMPETITION.

29:27.896 --> 29:30.725
-COME ON, HOBIE,
YOU CAN DO IT.

29:33.162 --> 29:35.512
-COME ON, HOBIE,
YOU CAN DO IT!

29:45.609 --> 29:48.351
-ANNOUNCER: AS THE TEAMS ROUND
THE PIER FOR THE FIRST LEG,

29:48.482 --> 29:51.180
BAYWATCH ONE WITH BUCHANNON
AND MICHAEL NEWMAN

29:51.311 --> 29:52.660
REMAINS IN THE LEAD.

29:52.791 --> 29:55.445
WITH BAYWATCH TWO,
MADISON AND DARIUS,

29:55.576 --> 29:59.580
AND ZUMA, BUCHANNON AND
DAWINGS BATTLING FOR SECOND.

30:01.321 --> 30:03.540
-COME ON, SMOOTH STROKE!

30:10.286 --> 30:12.941
-COME ON, HOBIE,
YOU CAN DO IT.

30:25.911 --> 30:29.131
-ANNOUNCER: ALL THREE
LEAD OUT TO TIDAL WAVE.

30:44.233 --> 30:47.367
-♪ COME CLOSER

30:49.673 --> 30:52.285
-ANNOUNCER: THE BOW MAN
REMAINS IN THE BOAT.

30:53.373 --> 30:55.984
THE STERN MAN
ROUNDS THE FLAG.

31:13.001 --> 31:14.916
ALL THE DORIES HAVE
TURNED AND MOVED

31:15.047 --> 31:17.310
ON TO THE LAST
LEG OF THE RACE.

31:17.440 --> 31:20.008
BAYWATCH ONE IS STILL
KEEPING ITS LEAD

31:20.139 --> 31:21.575
OVER THE COMPETITION.

31:33.456 --> 31:35.981
-[GROANING]

31:38.897 --> 31:39.898
-CHARLIE?

31:40.899 --> 31:42.291
-HON, ARE YOU OKAY?

31:43.423 --> 31:44.728
-YOU WATCH FOR ME.

31:58.220 --> 32:03.312
-[TRIUMPHANT MUSIC]

32:05.445 --> 32:06.794
-ANNOUNCER: UH, OH!
WATCH OUT!

32:06.925 --> 32:08.927
BAYWATCH ONE IS
BEING CHALLENGED

32:09.057 --> 32:13.670
AND BEATEN BY ZUMA'S HOBIE
BUCHANNON AND INGO DAWINGS.

32:13.801 --> 32:16.804
AND WE HAVE
A NEW LEADER!

32:32.733 --> 32:34.691
WE'RE COMING IN TO
THE HOME STRETCH!

32:34.822 --> 32:36.650
THROUGH THE SURF LINE!

32:49.924 --> 32:51.970
AND THEY'RE BEACHED,
THE BOW MAN HEADING

32:52.100 --> 32:53.449
FOR THE FINISH LINE.

32:53.580 --> 32:55.799
HOBIE BUCHANNON IS THE
FIRST OUT OF THE WATER.

32:55.930 --> 32:58.150
FOLLOWED CLOSELY BY
HIS FATHER MITCH.

32:58.280 --> 33:01.805
-[CHEERING AND APPLAUSE]

33:01.936 --> 33:04.112
IT'S A FOOT RACE
TO THE END!

33:04.243 --> 33:06.985
BUCHANNON AGAINST BUCHANNON!

33:10.292 --> 33:12.164
FOR THE FIRST TIME
IN SEVEN YEARS,

33:12.294 --> 33:13.687
WE HAVE A NEW
TAPLIN WINNER!

33:13.817 --> 33:15.732
HOBIE BUCHANNON
AND INGO DAWINGS!

33:15.863 --> 33:17.821
-FINALLY! THE
STREAK IS BROKEN!

33:17.952 --> 33:21.173
-I DON'T BELIEVE THIS.
AFTER SEVEN YEARS.

33:21.303 --> 33:22.522
YOU AREN'T UPSET?

33:23.740 --> 33:25.264
-OF COURSE I'M UPSET.

33:26.656 --> 33:28.745
AT LEAST IT STAYS
IN THE FAMILY.

33:28.876 --> 33:30.834
-YEAH, EASY FOR
YOU TO SAY.

33:30.965 --> 33:32.401
-THERE'S ALWAYS
NEXT YEAR.

33:34.142 --> 33:36.405
-WHAT DO YOU SAY WE GO
GIVE THIS TO CHARLIE?

33:37.406 --> 33:38.668
-I THINK THAT'S
A GREAT IDEA.

33:41.889 --> 33:42.846
-SHOULD'VE HAD YOU.

33:49.897 --> 33:51.116
-LET'S GO!

33:56.991 --> 33:58.906
THERE'S YOUR PROBLEM
RIGHT THERE, DAD.

33:59.037 --> 34:00.299
YOU'RE NOT BENDING
YOUR ELBOWS ENOUGH

34:00.429 --> 34:01.648
AT THE TOP OF
YOUR STROKE.

34:01.778 --> 34:03.954
-IN YOUR DREAMS,
HOBSTER, IN YOUR DREAMS.

34:04.085 --> 34:05.043
-JUST TRYING TO
HELP YOU OUT.

34:05.173 --> 34:07.219
-YEAH, RIGHT, SAVE IT.

34:10.699 --> 34:15.270
-[MELANCHOLY MUSIC]

34:15.400 --> 34:19.100
ALL RIGHT, MY DOOR, ALL
RIGHT, ALL RIGHT, EASY.

34:49.565 --> 34:53.960
-[SOMBER MUSIC]

37:10.010 --> 37:12.055
-I WANNA THANK
YOU FOR BEING HERE.

37:12.926 --> 37:16.886
FOR MY MOM AND FOR
ME AND FOR CHARLIE.

37:19.324 --> 37:21.369
CHARLIE THOUGHT THAT
LIFEGUARDS WERE HEROES

37:22.283 --> 37:27.245
AND HE WAS RIGHT, BUT CHARLIE
WAS A REAL HERO TOO, I THINK.

37:27.941 --> 37:30.117
HE CHOSE TO SPEND HIS
LAST DAYS IN AND OUT

37:30.248 --> 37:33.033
OF THE HOSPITAL INSTEAD OF
AT HOME WITH HIS FRIENDS

37:34.295 --> 37:36.384
BECAUSE HE WANTED TO
MAKE A DIFFERENCE.

37:37.951 --> 37:39.387
I'M SORRY.

37:46.264 --> 37:47.961
-CHARLIE DID
MAKE A DIFFERENCE.

37:48.570 --> 37:51.965
NOT ONLY 'CAUSE HE ALLOWED
THE DOCTORS TO DO RESEARCH

37:52.966 --> 37:56.578
TO HELP FIND THE GENE THAT
CAUSED THIS RARE FORM OF CANCER,

37:58.363 --> 38:03.150
BUT BECAUSE OF CHARLIE,
OTHER CHILDREN WILL LIVE.

38:03.281 --> 38:08.373
YOU SEE, IN HIS OWN WAY,
CHARLIE WAS A LIFEGUARD.

38:09.112 --> 38:12.551
CHARLIE IS STILL
SAVING LIVES.

38:12.681 --> 38:15.902
CHARLIE MADE A BIG DIFFERENCE
TO ALL OF US HERE AT BAYWATCH.

38:16.032 --> 38:18.818
JUST BY SPENDING
TIME WITH US.

38:20.210 --> 38:21.777
JUST BY BEING CHARLIE.

38:22.561 --> 38:27.217
WE WILL NEVER FORGET
HIS ENTHUSIASM FOR LIFE,

38:27.957 --> 38:29.959
HIS WILL TO LIVE,

38:31.570 --> 38:32.745
AND THAT SMILE,

38:34.834 --> 38:36.444
THAT WONDERFUL SMILE.

38:37.837 --> 38:41.362
CHARLIE, PAL, BELIEVE ME,

38:42.363 --> 38:45.758
YOU MADE A DIFFERENCE,
A BIG DIFFERENCE

38:46.715 --> 38:51.807
AND WE ARE GLAD THAT
YOU COULD BE HERE.

38:53.113 --> 38:57.509
-[SOMBER MUSIC]

41:36.058 --> 41:41.977
♪ I WANNA MAKE A
DIFFERENCE IN THIS WORLD ♪
